Google Weather module for Joomla 1.5
by computer - daten -netze | feeenders
http://www.feenders.de

/** INSTALLATION */
-------------------
* Install the "googleWeather Module" with the Joomla installation manager 
  as administrator in the backend.
* Create a new "googleWeather Module".
* Set module options like language or icons and location.

/** LIMIMITATIONS */
-------------------
* The mudule must get an xml-file from google. 
* Therefore "allow-url-fopen" should be enabled in the PHP configuration. (php.ini)
* Alternatively you can install the php-curl extention.

If you errors, open the customer-package-configuration of your provider.
There is often a possibility to switch from PHP4 to PHP5 an change values like
"allow-url-fopen".

/** USAGE */
------------
Set the Wather-location in module-configuration
 * singapore
 * berlin,germany
 * weather los angeles

* Customize layout by using "div.MOD_weather" and "img.MOD_weather" in your
  templates.css-file.

Example: 
	div.mod_weather {
		width: 300px;
		border: 1px solid black;
		background: #E0E5EF;
		padding: 5px;
		font-size: 10px;
	}

	img.mod_weather {
		margin: 0 0 0 20px;
		float: right;
	}


